String Functions
1) charAt()
Used to get a character at a specific position
Syntax: string.charAt(index)
Example: "Hello".charAt(1) → e

2) length()
Used to find total number of characters
Syntax: string.length()
Example: "Hello".length() → 5

3) toLowerCase()
Converts all letters to lowercase
Syntax: string.toLowerCase()
Example: "HELLO" → hello

4) toUpperCase()
Converts all letters to uppercase
Syntax: string.toUpperCase()
Example: "hello" → HELLO

5) split()
Splits string into parts using delimiter
Syntax: string.split("delimiter")
Example: "a,b,c".split(",") → a b c

6) replace()
Replaces old characters/words with new ones
Syntax: string.replace(old, new)
Example: "Hello".replace("H","Y") → Yello

7) substring()
Extracts part of a string
Syntax: string.substring(start, end)
Example: "Hello".substring(1,4) → ell

8) contains()
Checks if string contains a specific word
Syntax: string.contains("text")
Example: "Hello".contains("He") → true
